A non-governmental organization, Good Leadership Support Organization (GLSO) has said that there’s need for an attitudinal change if Nigeria must achieve the much desired growth and development in the country. The call was reechoed during an online press conference over the weekend in the build up to the Launch of President Muhammadu Buhari’s Political Ideology – The Third Way Principle. Speaking during the event, Bridget Torbua Igbauke, Director General of the organisation, said Nigerians must change their mindset, thinking, perception and attitude towards government policies if the country must continue on the path of progress. She emphasized the need to hold unto the political ideology, principles and policies of President Muhammadu Buhari, so together, the country can break the cycle of poverty. <img class="wp-image-235710 alignleft" src="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/bridget-torbua.png?resize=314%2C246&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="314" height="246" data-recalc-dims="1" />  “All the mechanism to breaking the circle of poverty has been laid bare on the table of social justice for everyone to access, without prejudice to gender religion, ethnicity, belief and creed. Therefore, we should drag ourselves to that water fountain of social justice and drink from it, employment, affordable education, health care, housing and food. “Employment is pivotal to breaking the circle of poverty .When you’re employed or an employer of labour, you earn an income or salary, when you earn money, you help yourself and family members to break out of poverty, you know how altruistic Africans/Nigerians can be and before long, we will all be waving poverty goodbye,” she said.